#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:173
#: f8f8b4f6cb4c416691f1df68866efc0c
msgid "Nonlinear systems: ``.nonlinear_solve()``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:175
#: dffe26bb94b94d9fa3f164935f6b9d44
msgid ""
"For problems where the residual ``F(u, params) = 0`` is nonlinear in "
"``u`` — hyperelasticity, plasticity, phase-field — use "
"``SparseMatrix.nonlinear_solve`` (inherited from "
"``torch_sla.SparseTensor``). The matrix is passed automatically into the "
"residual closure, the Jacobian is obtained through autograd, and the "
"backward pass uses the adjoint method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:200
#: f9568078f83e42378e3ac4c31e45d930
msgid "Key keyword arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:202
#: 6202eee251504348a1ce5a8fe971e384
msgid ""
"``method``: ``\"newton\"`` (default, Newton-Raphson with Armijo line "
"search), ``\"picard\"`` (fixed-point), or ``\"anderson\"`` (Anderson "
"acceleration)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:205
#: 5b18d82098f24f64bc428096ad0194e2
msgid "``line_search`` (default ``True``) — toggle Armijo backtracking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:206
#: acf6622bbd1e49d099766668f8c233db
msgid "``tol`` / ``atol`` / ``max_iter`` for the outer nonlinear loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:207
#: bb66cbaeada948058c911f6ad73b9fa1
msgid ""
"``linear_solver`` / ``linear_method`` to pick the backend used for each "
"inner linear solve."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:210
#: e46ca43b22df4deab1e8ecd34a188e1e
msgid ""
"The forward pass runs the chosen nonlinear iteration; the backward pass "
"solves a single adjoint system, so gradients of ``u`` w.r.t. any "
"``requires_grad`` parameter (including ``A.values``) cost roughly one "
"extra linear solve regardless of how many nonlinear iterations the "
"forward took."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:218
#: 78b8d2311d74462ba932faddd2884d57
msgid "Lower-level entry points (legacy)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:222
#: 85df116dd3c74d0eaaa81bb968b8f47b
msgid ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.spsolve` and "
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.nonlinear_solve` are TensorMesh-internal "
"fallbacks that pre-date the ``torch-sla`` integration. They are "
"**scheduled for removal**; the canonical solver path is the "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` (i.e. "
"``torch_sla.SparseTensor``) methods above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:229
#: a1eefb2639344c82a8b3b0e3f1b8e973
msgid ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.spsolve` is a free function that operates on raw"
" COO arrays ``(edata, row, col, shape, b)`` instead of a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` object. In practice this is "
"rarely useful — assembly produces a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix`, condensation produces a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix`, and ``K.solve(b)`` covers every"
" FEM workflow in this guide. ``tensormesh.sparse.spsolve`` will be "
"retired once the remaining call sites have moved over to "
"``SparseMatrix.solve`` / ``torch_sla.spsolve``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:238
#: 9b4299079bd74fbda29350a38b413c8f
msgid ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.nonlinear_solve` is the in-tree Newton-Raphson "
"helper. It requires the user to supply an explicit Jacobian closure and "
"lacks line search, Picard / Anderson modes, and the autograd-based "
"Jacobian assembly that ``torch_sla.SparseTensor.nonlinear_solve`` "
"provides. Migrate to ``A.nonlinear_solve(residual, u0, *params)``."
msgstr ""

